{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> παίζω</b>, <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>παίσδω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.42 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: <i>Laconian dialect</i> <i>present</i> <i>participle</i> <i>genitive</i> <i>plural</i> <i>feminine</i> <b>παιδδωἇν</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 1313 (Lyric poetry): \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> παιξοῦμαι Syrac. in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 9.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], παίξομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.2Ki.6.21, “Anthologia Graeca” 12.46 (3rd c.BC: Asclepiades Epigrammaticus), παίξω [prev. work] 211 (2nd c.AD: Strato Epigrammaticus), “Anacreontea” 41.8\">LXX+3rd c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist 1</i> ἔπαισα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (see. below), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 1055, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> πέπαικα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 923.3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i> πέπαισμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.77 (variant{πέπλασται}), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 1227; _imperative_ πεπαίσθω 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 278d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also <i>aorist</i> ἔπαιξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Crates Comicus 23, 5th-6th c.BC: Ctesias Historicus “fragment” 29.59, LXX.Judg.16.25, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DDeor.” 6.4, etc.\">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> πέπαιχα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Demosthenes” 9 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>aorist</i> ἐπαίχθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.123f, 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 8.6 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> πέπαιγμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “epigram Gr.” 979.3 (from Philae)\">Refs</a>]; <i>infinitive</i> πεπαῖχθαι Timarch. cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 11.501f; _imperative_ πεπαίχθω 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Mus.” p.106 K., Fronto “Epig.Gr.” 5.86: 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] uses only <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i>, and (in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.251) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> <i>imperative</i> παίσατ; Trag. only <i>present</i>: (παῖς):—properly, <b>play like a child, sport</b>, τῇ δέ θ᾽ ἅμα Νύμφαι.. ἀγρονόμοι παίζουσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.106, compare 7.291 (never in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad”), 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.114, etc.: _metaphorically_, αἰὼν παῖς ἐστὶ παίζων 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus 52. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> especially <b>dance</b>, παίσατε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.251; δῶμα περιστεναχίζετο ποσσὶν ἀνδρῶν παιζόντων 23.147, compare 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 277; π. τε καὶ χορεύειν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 409, compare 390; ἐνόπλια χαλκωθεὶς ἔπαιζεν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.86:\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, ἀλλὰ πέπαισται μετρίως ἡμῖν, of the chorus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 1227. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>play</b> [a game], σφαίρῃ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.100; κλεψύδρῃ 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 100.9 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κύβοις ἐπὶ συνθήκαις π. Ctes.[same place]; ἀντ᾽ ἀστραγάλων κονδύλοισι π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 43, compare 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 92 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. διὰ γραμμῆς (see. γραμμή[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" III. 2); π. πρὸς κότταβον 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Comicus 46.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μετά τινων with others, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.114: with _accusative_ _cognate_, κότταβον ἀγκύλῃ π. 6th c.BC: Anacreon Lyricus 53 (uncertain); σφαῖραν 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Alexander” 73; π. παιδιὰν πρός τινα 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 1055, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus Alcaeus1.110b\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; κύνα καὶ πόλιν π., of a game similar to our draughts, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 56: with _adverbs_, φαινίνδα π. 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 283, compare 5th c.BC: Crates Comicus [same place], etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>play</b> on a musical instrument, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Apollinem” 206: with _accusative_, Πὰν ὁ καλαμόφθογγα παίζων 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 230 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>dance and sing</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 1.16. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>play amorously</b>, πρὸς ἀλλήλους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 9.2; μετά τινος LXX.Gen.26.8 \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]; of mares, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 572a30. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> <b>hunt, pursue game</b>, π. κατ᾽ ἄλσος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 567. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>jest, sport</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.28, 5.4, 9.11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to σπουδάζω, [<a h