script:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.1090f; τὸ Μενεδήμῳ πεπαιγμένον [prev. work]81e; but οἷα πέπαιγμαι, in _active_ sense, “epigram Gr.” 979.3 (from Philae). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i>, <b>play with, make sport of</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nigr.” 20, “Anthologia Graeca” 10.64 (6th c.AD: Agathias Historicus et Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> Grammars, of words <b>played upon</b> or <b>coined for the joke's sake</b>, οἱ κωμῳδοὶ παίζειν εἰώθασι τὰ τοιαῦτα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 42, compare 68, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3815","accentedUnicode":"παίζω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3816","matchingForm":"παῖς","stepTransliteration":"pais","gloss":"child","_zh_tw_Gloss":"僕人","_es_Gloss":"niño","_zh_Gloss":"仆人"}],"shortDef":"to indulge in revelry, play, amuse oneself, dance, sometimes a euphemism for sexual immorality","mediumDef":"to indulge in revelry, play, amuse oneself, dance, sometimes a euphemism for sexual immorality <br /><b>to play in the manner of children; to sport, indulge in revelry, amuse oneself, to practise the festive gestures</b>, of idolatrous worship, <ref='1Co.10.7'>1Cor. 10:7</ref>*","stepGloss":"to play","stepTransliteration":"paizō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"bailar, jugar, divertirse","_zh_tw_Definition":"玩耍, 自找樂趣 (林前 10:7)","_zh_Definition":"玩耍, 自找乐趣 (林前 10:7)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"chơi như một đứa trẻ; chơi đùa","_zh_tw_Gloss":"玩耍","_es_Gloss":"jugar","_zh_Gloss":"玩耍"}]}